# TicketScout — Cloudflare Pages redirects
#
# ROUTING ARCHITECTURE:
# - /concert/[slug]  → static file at concert/[slug].html  (no redirect needed)
# - /football/[slug] → static file at football/[slug].html (no redirect needed)
# - /theatre/[slug]  → static file at theatre/[slug].html  (no redirect needed)
# - /venue/[slug]    → static file at venue/[slug].html    (no redirect needed)
#
# Static files in subfolders are served automatically by Cloudflare Pages.
# Functions in functions/[category]/[slug].js are a FALLBACK for unknown slugs only.
# Do NOT add catch-all redirects for any of the above paths — they will break static routing.
#
# WHEN ADDING A NEW CATEGORY (e.g. /comedy, /sports):
# 1. Create a [category].html template at the repo root
# 2. Create static HTML files in a [category]/ folder (one per item)
# 3. Add functions/api/[category].js for the data API
# 4. Add the landing page rule below: /[category] /[category].html 200
# 5. Do NOT add a catch-all /[category]/* redirect — it will break subpages
# 6. Optionally add functions/[category]/[slug].js as catch-all for unknown slugs
#    (but test carefully — worker errors will show as 1101)

# Category landing pages — serve the template for the base path (no slug)
/concerts  /concert.html   200
/football  /football.html  200
/theatre   /theatre.html   200
